Blocks.Text: - Membranous nephropathy, consistent with lupus nephritis ISN/RPS class V.
Moderate interstitial fibrosis and tubular atrophy
Moderate arteriosclerosis, and diffuse and focally marked arteriolar hyalinosis.
There are no active lesions in the sampled cortex. Compared to the patient's previous biopsy (see S02-20733,
10/30/2002), there has been a mild interval increase in the extent of glomerular and tubulointerstitial scarring.
Interpretation performed by the Attending Pathologist.
Electronically Signed Out by Kammi J. Henriksen, M.D.
The patient is a 55 year old female with a history of systemic lupus erythematosus. A prior kidney biopsy in
2002 showed membranous lupus nephritis (see S02-20733, 10/30/2002). Her lupus has been well controlled,
but she recently had increased proteinuria (UPCR - - 421 mg/gm several months ago, previously normal) and
microscopic hematuria. Renal function is currently stable (serum creatinine - 1.5 mg/dL).
B: Native renal biopsy for Immunofluorescence
C: Native renal biopsy for electron microscopy
Received in formalin for light microscopy are 2 cores measuring 0.8-1.0 cm in length. Received in Michel's
solution for immunofluorescence microscopy are 3 cores measuring 0.8-1.2 cm in length. Received in
glutaraldehyde for electron microscopy are 4 cores measuring 0.2-2.0 cm in length.
